Zoran Zaev, Prime Minister of Macedonia, his wife Zorica and his son Dushko cast their vote in Macedonia’s referendum on a name change for the country that would open the way to join NATO and the European Union in Strumica (Macedonia) on September 30, 2018.
In front of parliament in Skopje, Vladimir Kavardarkov, 54, was preparing a small stage and removing chairs in front of tents planted by those who were going to boycott the referendum.
